# AgentFlow secrets — example file.
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env:        cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in the values below (no quotes needed).
# 3. Export into your shell:        set -a; source .env; set +a
# 4. NEVER commit .env — it holds real tokens. Only commit .env.example.
#
# These names are the canonical ENV VAR names AgentFlow reads. In
# .claude/agentflow.yaml, each connection's `auth.token_env` points at one of
# these names, and `mcp.server` names which .mcp.json server the token powers:
#   connections.github.auth.token_env: GITHUB_TOKEN  →  mcp.server "github"
#   connections.github_project.auth.token_env: GITHUB_TOKEN  →  mcp.server "github" (+ "project" scope)
#   connections.figma.auth.token_env: FIGMA_TOKEN    →  mcp.server "figma"
# The MCP servers in .mcp.json resolve them via ${GITHUB_TOKEN} / ${FIGMA_TOKEN}.

# GITHUB_TOKEN (required) — GitHub personal access token.
#   Scopes: repo (always); + project (only if connections.github_project is enabled, for a Projects v2 board).
#   Fine-grained tokens are preferred. Powers the "github" MCP server (used by
#   both connections.github and connections.github_project).
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# FIGMA_TOKEN (optional) — Figma personal access token.
#   Only needed if connections.figma is enabled. Powers the "figma" MCP server;
#   when unset that server is inert and figma-design features are skipped.
FIGMA_TOKEN=
